# RNAseq analysis conda environment

This repository contains scripts to create and maintain the `RNAseq` conda
environment and install required R/Bioconductor packages for RNA-seq analyses.
This includes R and Python tools for bulk, single-cell, and spatial
transcriptomics data processing and visualization. 

## What this repository does

1. Creates or updates the `RNAseq` conda environment from `RNAseq_analysis.yaml`.
   This step installs all CRAN R packages via the YAML. This ensures any package dependencies are met and available in the environment.
1. Updates already installed R packages inside that environment. This ensures all 
   packages are up to date with the latest versions (the conda versions may not always be the latest).
1. Installs requested Bioconductor/GitHub R packages.
1. Checks installation logs for failures.

## Main files

1. `Makefile`: Orchestrates environment creation, package updates, and checks.
1. `RNAseq_analysis.yaml`: Conda environment definition.
1. `xInstallPackages.sh`: Iterates through package list and calls R installer.
1. `xrInstallPackage.R`: Installs individual R packages (Bioconductor/GitHub).
1. `xUpdateRPackages.R`: Updates installed R packages and writes change logs.
1. `PackagesToInstall.txt`: Package list consumed by installer scripts.

## Usage

Run the full workflow:

```bash
make
```

This runs:

1. `create-env`
1. `update-packages`
1. `install-packages`
1. `check-logs`

### Run steps individually

```bash
make create-env
make update-packages
make install-packages
make check-logs
```

## R package update step

The `update-packages` target updates R packages using:

```bash
conda run -n RNAseq Rscript xUpdateRPackages.R "$(CRAN_MIRROR)" "$(R_UPDATE_LOG)"
```

Default values (defined in `Makefile`):

1. `CRAN_MIRROR=https://cloud.r-project.org`
1. `R_UPDATE_LOG=AllPackageInstallationLogs/00_RPackageUpdate.log`

Override at runtime if needed:

```bash
make update-packages CRAN_MIRROR=https://cran.rstudio.com
make update-packages R_UPDATE_LOG=AllPackageInstallationLogs/custom_update.log
```

## Logs

1. Per-package install logs: `AllPackageInstallationLogs/`
1. Update summary log: `AllPackageInstallationLogs/00_RPackageUpdate.log`
1. Overall status summary: `AllPackageInstallationSummary.log`

If `check-logs` finds any `FAILURE`, it exits with error and keeps logs for review.
If no failures are found, logs are cleaned up.

## Requirements

1. `conda` and `mamba` available in shell.
1. Network access to the selected CRAN mirror and package sources.
1. Build tools available for source package compilation when needed.